      "source": [
        "# Taking rest 30% of data as Testing data\n",

        "datadfTest = datadf[~datadf.apply(tuple,1).isin(datadfTrain.apply(tuple,1))]"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Hyperparameters for the feedforward neural network\n",
        "\n",
        "input_size = 38\n",
        "hidden_size = 20\n",
        "num_classes = 3\n",
        "num_epochs = 20\n",
        "batch_size = 1\n",
        "learning_rate = 0.001\n",
        "\n",
        "device = torch.device('cuda:0' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Rn7x5vXyHhVU"
      },
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Feedforward neural network\n",
        "\n",
        "class NeuralNet(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size, num_classes):\n",
        "        super(NeuralNet, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, hidden_size) \n",
        "        self.relu = nn.ReLU()\n",
        "        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(hidden_size, num_classes)  \n",
        "    \n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        out = self.fc1(x)\n",
        "        out = self.relu(out)\n",
        "        out = self.fc2(out)\n",
        "        return out"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nblqGz1QHhXE"
      },
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Code to assign the dataset as Tensors, so that we will be able to use it with neural net\n",
        "\n",
        "class GetData(Dataset):\n",
        "  def __init__(self, df):\n",
        "    \n",
        "    x = df.iloc[0:df.shape[0], 1:df.shape[1]].to_numpy(dtype = numpy.float32)\n",
        "    y = df.iloc[0:df.shape[0], 0].to_numpy(dtype = numpy.int32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    sc = StandardScaler()\n",
        "    x_train = sc.fit_transform(x)\n",
        "    #x_train = x\n",
        "    x_train = x_train.astype(numpy.float32)\n",
        "    y_train = y\n",
        "\n",
        "    self.x_train = torch.tensor(x_train)#, dtype = torch.float32)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    self.y_train = torch.tensor(y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def __len__(self):\n",
        "    return len(self.y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def __getitem__(self, idx):\n",
        "    return self.x_train[idx], self.y_train[idx]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3hf98lY1HhZA"
      },
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Transformation of initial Training set to Tensor datatype\n",
        "\n",
        "train_dataset = GetData(datadfTrain)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "00FRX29GHha2"
      },
      "execution_count": 17,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Transformation of initial Testing set to Tensor datatype\n",
        "\n",
        "test_dataset = GetData(datadfTest)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vKlIvAodHhch"
      },
      "execution_count": 18,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Creating loaders\n",
        "\n",
        "train_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(dataset=train_dataset,\n",
        "                                           batch_size=batch_size, \n",
        "                                           shuffle=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "test_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(dataset=test_dataset,\n",
        "                                          batch_size=batch_size, \n",
        "                                          shuffle=False)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "siP-yVQ6Hhet"
      },
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Training and accuracy of the net\n",
        "\n",
        "model_NN = NeuralNet(input_size, hidden_size, num_classes).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Loss and optimizer\n",
        "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
        "optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model_NN.parameters(), lr=learning_rate, weight_decay=0.00001)  \n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the model_NN\n",
        "total_step = len(train_loader)\n",
        "test_acc_list, train_acc_list = [], []\n",
        "for epoch in range(num_epochs):\n",
        "    for i, (features, score) in enumerate(train_loader):  \n",
        "        # Move tensors to the configured device\n",
        "        features = features.to(device)\n",
        "        score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "        score = score.to(device)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Forward pass\n",
        "        outputs = model_NN(features)\n",
        "        loss = criterion(outputs, score)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Backward and optimize\n",
        "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "        loss.backward()\n",
        "        optimizer.step()\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if (i+1) % 100 == 0:\n",
        "            print ('Epoch [{}/{}], Step [{}/{}], Loss: {:.4f}' \n",
        "                   .format(epoch+1, num_epochs, i+1, total_step, loss.item()))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Test the model_NN\n",
        "    # In test phase, we don't need to compute gradients (for memory efficiency)\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        total = 0\n",
        "        for features, score in test_loader:\n",
        "            features = features.to(device)\n",
        "            score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "            score = score.to(device)\n",
        "            \n",
        "            outputs = model_NN(features)\n",
        "            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)\n",
        "            total += score.size(0)\n",
        "            correct += (predicted == score).sum().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "        print('Accuracy of the network on the 10000 test images: {} %'.format(100 * correct / total))\n",
        "        test_acc_list.append(100 * correct / total)\n",
        "\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        total = 0\n",
        "        for features, score in train_loader:\n",
        "            features = features.to(device)\n",
        "            score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "            score = score.to(device)\n",
        "            \n",
        "            outputs = model_NN(features)\n",
        "            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)\n",
        "            total += score.size(0)\n",
        "            correct += (predicted == score).sum().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "        print('Accuracy of the network on the training images: {} %'.format(100 * correct / total))\n",
        "        train_acc_list.append(100 * correct / total)\n",
        "\n",
        "        \n",
        "        \n",
        "plt.plot(train_acc_list, '-b', label='train acc')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_acc_list, '-r', label='test acc')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=60)\n",
        "plt.title('Accuracy ~ Epoch')\n",
        "# plt.savefig('assets/accr_{}.png'.format(cfg_idx))\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save the model_NN checkpoint\n",
        "torch.save(model_NN.state_dict(), 'model_NN.ckpt')"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Hyperparameters for the feedforward network with two hidden layers\n",
        "\n",
        "input_size = 38        # 28 * 28\n",
        "hidden_size = 20       # the output dimension of the linear model in each MLP hidden layer\n",
        "num_classes = 3        # the number of classes\n",
        "num_epochs = 20         # the number of epochs (each epoch: scanning the entire training set)\n",
        "batch_size = 1        # how many samples are used in each iteration of SGD/Adam update\n",
        "learning_rate = 0.001 "
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_SDGP-q2Hvfq"
      },
      "execution_count": 21,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Feedforward network with two hidden layers and trining + accuracies\n",
        "\n",
        "class NeuralNet2Layer(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size, num_classes):\n",
        "        super(NeuralNet2Layer, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, hidden_size) \n",
        "        self.relu1 = nn.ReLU()\n",
        "        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(hidden_size, hidden_size)\n",
        "        self.relu2 = nn.ReLU()\n",
        "        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(hidden_size, num_classes)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        out = self.fc1(x)\n",
        "        out = self.relu1(out)\n",
        "        out = self.fc2(out)\n",
        "        out = self.relu2(out)\n",
        "        out = self.fc3(out)\n",
        "\n",
        "        return out\n",
        "\n",
        "model = NeuralNet2Layer(input_size, hidden_size, num_classes).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define loss function and optimization algorithm (optimizer)\n",
        "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
        "optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=learning_rate, weight_decay=0.00001)  \n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the model\n",
        "# train_acc_list, test_acc_list = [],[]\n",
        "total_step = len(train_loader)\n",
        "test_acc_list, train_acc_list = [], []\n",
        "for epoch in range(num_epochs):\n",
        "    for i, (features, score) in enumerate(train_loader):  \n",
        "        # Move tensors to the configured device\n",
        "        features = features.reshape(-1, 38).to(device)\n",
        "        score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "        score = score.to(device)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Forward pass\n",
        "        outputs = model(features)\n",
        "        loss = criterion(outputs, score)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Backward and optimize\n",
        "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "        loss.backward()\n",
        "        optimizer.step()\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if (i+1) % 100 == 0:\n",
        "            print ('Epoch [{}/{}], Step [{}/{}], Loss: {:.4f}' \n",
        "                   .format(epoch+1, num_epochs, i+1, total_step, loss.item()))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Test the model and plot training/testing accuracy\n",
        "    # In test phase, we don't need to compute gradients \n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        total = 0\n",
        "        for features, score in test_loader:\n",
        "            features = features.reshape(-1, 38).to(device)\n",
        "            score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "            score = score.to(device)\n",
        "            outputs = model(features)\n",
        "            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)\n",
        "            total += score.size(0)\n",
        "            correct += (predicted == score).sum().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "        print('Accuracy of the network on the 10000 test images: {} %'.format(100 * correct / total))\n",
        "        test_acc_list.append(100 * correct / total)\n",
        "\n",
        "        \n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        total = 0\n",
        "        for features, score in train_loader:\n",
        "            features = features.reshape(-1, 38).to(device)\n",
        "            score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "            score = score.to(device)\n",
        "            outputs = model(features)\n",
        "            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)\n",
        "            total += score.size(0)\n",
        "            correct += (predicted == score).sum().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "        print('Accuracy of the network on the training images: {} %'.format(100 * correct / total))\n",
        "        train_acc_list.append(100 * correct / total)\n",
        "            \n",
        "plt.plot(train_acc_list, '-b', label='train acc')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_acc_list, '-r', label='test acc')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=60)\n",
        "plt.title('Accuracy ~ Epoch')\n",
        "# plt.savefig('assets/accr_{}.png'.format(cfg_idx))\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "        \n",
        "# Save the model checkpoint\n",
        "torch.save(model.state_dict(), 'model2Layer.ckpt')"
      ],

      "source": [
        "# Calculating the profit using 3 popular strategies:\n",
        "# 1) Flat strategy: use same amount for every bet. Normally - 5% of initial amount of money. Conservative and less risky if the accuracy of betting predictions is legit. But doesn't give much money\n",
        "# 2) Martingale strategy: initial bet is 5% of the initial amount of money. If the bet is lost, double the bet (it becomes 10% of the initial amount).\n",
        "# If we lose again - double previous one (20%) and so on until we win. Risky strat, requires to have a lot of backup money in case of a long losestreak but is the best in terms of getting more money.\n",
        "# 3) 2-6 strategy: requires to win at least 2 out of 6 bets (33%). We start with 5% of the initial bank. Then no matter what outcome, we double the bet for the next prediction.\n",
        "# If won - we end the series and start a new one with 5% of initial bank. If lost - we use x4 of initial bet. If lost again - x6, then if lost once more - x8 and if this one is lost as well, x12. \n",
        "# (max 6 bets in series). If x12 is lost, we start again from x1 of 5%. Whenever we win twice in one series of bets (x1, x2, x4, x6, x8, x12), we end the series and start over again.\n",
        "# 2-6 is the best strat I know so far, since it's relaible, not much risk involved but the outcome is much higher than the Flat strat. Also, you only need accuracy of 33% to earn money.\n",
        "\n",
        "money = 10000\n",
        "flat = 0.05 * money\n",
        "batch_size = 1\n",
        "i = 0\n",
        "k = 0\n",
        "p = 0\n",
        "money_list = []\n",
        "twoSixList = [1,2,4,6,8,12]\n",
        "nu = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "#strategies\n",
        "\n",
        "Flat = False # Flat strat\n",
        "MGale = False # Martingale strat\n",
        "twoToSix = True # 2-6 strat\n",
        "\n",
        "with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        total = 0\n",
        "          \n",
        "        for features, score in test_loader:\n",
        "              \n",
        "          features = features.reshape(-1, 38).to(device)\n",
        "          score = score.type(torch.LongTensor)\n",
        "          score = score.to(device)\n",
        "          outputs = model(features)\n",
        "          _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)\n",
        "          total += score.size(0)\n",
        "          correct += (predicted == score).sum().item()\n",
        "          if (MGale == True):\n",
        "            if (predicted.item() == score.item()):\n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              win = flat * math.pow(2,k) * (coef-1)\n",
        "              money += win\n",
        "              k = 0\n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, won: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, win, money))\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "              loss = flat * math.pow(2,k)\n",
        "              money -= loss\n",
        "              k += 1\n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, lost: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, loss, money))\n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "          if (Flat == True):\n",
        "            if (predicted.item() == score.item()):\n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              money += flat * (coef-1)\n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, won: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, flat * (coef-1), money))\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "              money -= flat\n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, lost: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, flat, money))\n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "          if (twoToSix == True):\n",
        "            if (predicted.item() == score.item()):\n",
        "              \n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              win = flat * (coef-1) * twoSixList[nu]\n",
        "              money += win\n",
        "              \n",
        "              \n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "              p += 1\n",
        "              nu += 1\n",
        "              if p == 2:\n",
        "                p = 0\n",
        "                nu = 0\n",
        "              if nu == 6:\n",
        "                nu = 0\n",
        "              \n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, won: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, win, money))\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "              loss = flat * twoSixList[nu]\n",
        "              money -= loss\n",
        "              coef = datadfTest.iloc[i, predicted.item() + 4]\n",
        "              nu += 1\n",
        "              if (nu == 6):\n",
        "                nu = 0\n",
        "                #print(i)\n",
        "              \n",
        "              print('match: {}, predicted side: {}, won side: {}, coef: {}, lost: {:.1f}, total: {}'. format(i, predicted.item(), score.item(), coef, loss, money))\n",
        "              money_list.append(money)\n",
        "          i+=1\n",
        "\n",
        "        \n",
        "        print(money)\n",
        "        print(total)\n",
        "        print(correct)\n",
        "\n",
        "        print('Accuracy of the network on test games: {} %'.format(100 * correct / total))\n",
        "        test_acc_list.append(100 * correct / total)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(money_list, '-b', label='money')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Money')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Match')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=60)\n",
        "plt.title('Money ~ Match')\n",
